{
  "texts": [
    "Forward-looking perspectives highlighted the potential of multimodal models and the ongoing evolution of AI technologies.",
    "The methodology, with its structured approach, offered a wide array toward understanding of the diverse facets shaping contemporary artificial intelligence (AI) within a framework, an experimentational simulation for generative AI model set for visualization.",
    "Generative artificial intelligence (generative AI or GenAI) refers to artificial intelligence capable of producing text, images, or other media using generative models.",
    "These models learn patterns and structures from training data to generate new data with similar characteristics.",
    "Notable examples include large language model (LLM) chatbots like ChatGPT, Copilot, Bard, and LLaMA, as well as text-to-image AI art systems such as Stable Diffusion, Midjourney, and DALL-E [11]."
  ]
}